    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "55538f27_8f2ae657",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/search_builds_verification.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T09:46:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is not in a spawned goroutine by the main flow. After 5 seconds, the `verifySearch()` would return with the python responses to the caller - `SearchBuilds()`, which would return those results to users. \n\nThe reason I added a timeout here is to not be block so long in case the `searchBuildsGoPath()` takes 5 seconds longer than python service. Because the users are still waiting for the response. If the \ngo path takes much longer than py path (which is highly unlikely happen), then just give up the later comparison and directly return.",
      "parentUuid": "a1d27d77_4134e08f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 93,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 93,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "035af625349f0c6a168a6768b98ffe57f34005ac",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b1d0ce5c_f018f5c5",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/search_builds_verification.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T18:56:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i understand why it is done. My concern is that it is not complete because the goroutine started in L73 will be still running after this goroutine exits. Moreover, the above goroutine will never exit because it will block on sending to goResCh (because nobody is receiving from it).\n\ni recommend:\n\n  goResCtx, cancelGoRes :\u003d context.WithCancel(ctx)\n  go func() {\n    goRes, goErr :\u003d searchBuildsGoPath(goResCtx, req)\n    goResCh \u003c- \u0026searchResponseBundle{res: goRes, err: goErr}\n  }()  \n\nthen here \n\n  cancelGoRes()\n  \u003c-goResCh\n\nthis way we tell that goroutine to stop immediately, but also wait for it stop",
      "parentUuid": "55538f27_8f2ae657",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 93,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 93,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "035af625349f0c6a168a6768b98ffe57f34005ac",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
